{"id":14880917,"mediaExerciseId":"ac7b5ff9-2bbd-4218-8e8e-e19ecd8802f9","exerciseName":"19","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612293,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":148,"solutions":[{"id":6073279,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In 2 years we will receive $20,000 and when that happens we plan to invest them at a 6.8% per annum rate. We need to calculate the future value of our funds after 6 years after we started investing. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We know the following data:\n\n|||\n|--|--|\nPV\t|$20,000\nt\t|6\nReturn rate|\t6.80%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To calculate know the Future Value (FV) of our investment we need to use the formula for it.\n\n$$ FV = {PV}\\cdot{(1+r)^t} $$\n\n*Where:*\n- PV is the present value\n- r is the applied rate\n- t is the periods of time the rate is applied\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Now we need to compute the formula with the given data to obtain the FV.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nFV &={\\$20,000}\\cdot{(1+0.068)^6} \\\\\n& = \\boxed{\\$29,679.56}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe future value of our money at the end of the 8 years we waited since we received them and invest them is **$29,679.56**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"FV = $29,679.56","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"21dbec56-8b33-48f3-a57a-0855bc97d009","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880918,"exerciseName":"20","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e2599586-731c-4760-b58b-02014fa0d372","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-20-e2599586-731c-4760-b58b-02014fa0d372"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880916,"exerciseName":"18","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"4a703296-7efd-4454-abd8-a9265ae6a5b7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-18-4a703296-7efd-4454-abd8-a9265ae6a5b7"},{"id":14880915,"exerciseName":"17","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d66ad92d-7c91-4a32-b9f2-220f783ccb57","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-17-d66ad92d-7c91-4a32-b9f2-220f783ccb57"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-19-ac7b5ff9-2bbd-4218-8e8e-e19ecd8802f9"}